      "ingredients": "4 (4 to 6 oz. each) Alaska Salmon steaks or fillets, thawed if necessary\r\n\r\n1/4 C peanut oil\r\n2 Tbs. soy sauce\r\n2 Tbs. balsamic vinegar\r\n2 Tbs. chopped green onions\r\n1-1/2 tsp. brown sugar\r\n1 clove garlic, minced\r\n3/4 tsp. grated ginger\r\n1/2 tsp. red chili flakes (or more to taste)\r\n1/2 tsp. sesame oil\r\n1/8 tsp. salt",
      "instructions": "Place salmon steaks or fillets in a glass dish.  Whisk together remaining ingredients and pour over salmon.  Cover with plastic wrap and marinate in refrigerator 4-6 hours.  Remove salmon from marinade and place on a well oiled grill 5 inches from coals.  Grill for 10 minutes per inch of thickness, measured at thickest part, or until fish just flakes when tested with a fork.  Turn halfway through cooking.",
