      "id": 280,
      "name": "Porcupine Meatballs",
      "ingredients": "1 egg, beaten\r\n1 10-3/4 oz. can tomato soup\r\n1/4 C uncooked rice (white)\r\n1/4 tsp. onion powder\r\n1/4 tsp. pepper\r\n1 lb. ground beef\r\n1 tsp. wooster sauce\r\n1/2 tsp. oregano\r\n",
      "instructions": "Combine egg, rice, onion powder and pepper.  Add beef, mix well.  Form into 15-20 balls, place into large skillet.  Mix soup, wooster sauce, oregano and 1/2 cup water, pour over meatballs, bring to boil.  Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20-25 minutes.",
