      "ingredients": "4 slices French bread\r\n4 tsp. olive oil\r\n1 large garlic clove, peeled\r\n\r\n1/2 lb. tomatoes, seeded, cut into 1/3-inch pieces\r\n1/2 tsp. sugar\r\n1 tsp. rice vinegar\r\n1/4 C chopped fresh basil\r\nsalt and pepper to taste",
      "instructions": "Preheat oven to 375.  Arrange bread slices on large baking sheet.  Brush bread with 2 teaspoons oil.  Bake until bread is toasted and golden brown, about 10 minutes.  Rub toasts with garlic.\r\n     Mix tomatoes, basil, 2 teaspoons olive oil and sugar in a small bowl.  Season to taste with salt and pepper.  Spoon 2 tablespoons tomato topping on each toast.  Arrange on platter and serve.",
