      "name": "Cumin-Dusted Salmon Fillets",
      "ingredients": "1 tsp. ground cumin\r\n1 tsp. paprika\r\n1/2 tsp. salt\r\n1/2 tsp. freshly ground black pepper\r\n4 (6-oz.) salmon fillets (about 1-inch thick), skinned\r\nCooking spray",
      "instructions": "Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.  Sprinkle both sides of fish with spice mixture.\r\n     Heat a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium heat, and add fish.  Cook 6 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.",
