      "id": 384,
      "name": "Barbecue Tofu Sandwiches",
      "ingredients": "1 (12 oz.) packaged extra firm tofu\r\n3 Tbs. vegetable oil\r\n1 onion, thinly sliced\r\n1 small can mushrooms\r\n1-1/2 C barbecue sauce\r\n6 hamburger buns",
      "instructions": "Slice tofu into 1/4-inch thick slices and drain between paper towels until most of the water has been squeezed out.  Cut tofu into strips.\r\n     Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet, fry tofu strips until golden brown on both sides.  Add onion and cook for a few minutes, until onion is at your desired consistency.\r\n     Add barbecue sauce and mushrooms.  Cook the mixture for ten minutes on low and serve on buns.",
