      "ingredients": "3 lbs. ground beef\r\n3 C chopped onions\r\n6 garlic cloves, finely chopped\r\n1/2 C chili powder\r\n2 cans (10.5oz.) beef consume\r\n1 can (14.5oz) beef broth\r\n2 C canned crushed tomatoes with added puree\r\n1/2 C stout or dark beer\r\n2 Tbs. minced canned chipotle chilies\r\n\r\n2 Tbs. yellow cornmeal\r\n3 cans (15.5oz.) black beans, drained, rinsed",
      "instructions": "Heat heavy large pot over high heat.  Add beef; sautÃ© until cooked through, breaking up meat with spoon, about 8 minutes.  Transfer to large bowl.  Add onions and garlic to same pot.  SautÃ© until onions are tender, about 8 minutes.  Add chili powder.  SautÃ© until fragrant, 3 minutes.  Add beef, broth, tomatoes, stout and chilies.  Cover partially; simmer until chili is thick, stirring often, about 1 hour 10 minutes.\r\n     Gradually stir cornmeal into chili.  Stir in beans.  Simmer until heated through.  Season generously with salt and pepper.  (Can be made 1 day ahead.  Cover and chill.  Rewarm over medium heat.)\r\n     Whisk sour cream, lime juice and lime peel in small bowl.  Season with salt.  Spoon chili into bowls.",
