      "name": "Basic Pie Crust (Carole's)",
      "ingredients": "4 C flour\r\n1-3/4 C shortening\r\n2 tsp. salt\r\n1 Tbs. sugar\r\n1/2 C water\r\n1 egg, slightly beaten\r\n1 Tbs. vinegar",
      "instructions": "In a large bowl combine flour, salt and sugar.  Cut shortening into flour mixture.  Mix together water, egg and vinegar.  Add to flour/shortening mixture, mix together and form into a smooth ball, but don't over-mix.  Chill 15 minutes.  Divide into 4 balls.",
