      "name": "Cranberry Walnut Bread",
      "ingredients": "2 C flour\r\n3/4 C sugar\r\n1 Tbs. baking powder\r\n1/2 tsp. salt\r\n1 C cranberries, coarsely chopped\r\n1/2 C chopped, toasted walnuts\r\n1 tsp. grated lemon zest\r\n1 tsp. grated orange zest\r\n2 eggs\r\n1 C milk\r\n1/4 C unsalted butter, melted",
      "instructions": "In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.  Stir in cranberries, walnuts, lemon and orange zest.  Set aside.  In another bowl, whisk eggs, milk and butter.  Make a well in center of flour mixture and pour in egg mixture stirring with a fork just until dry mixture is moistened.  Pour the mixture into greased and floured 9x5-inch loaf pan.  Bake at 350 until top is golden-brown and toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean (60 minutes).  Cool 15 minutes.  Remove from pan; cool on a rack.  Makes 1 loaf.",
