      "ingredients": "2 Tbs. butter\r\n1 medium onion, grated\r\n1 tsp. minced fresh ginger\r\n1-1/2 tsp. curry powder\r\n1 tsp. ground coriander\r\n1/2 tsp. cinnamon\r\n1/2 tsp. cumin\r\n1 (14.5oz.) can diced tomatoes\r\n1 (15oz.) can chickpeas, drained\r\n3/4 lb. red or Yukon gold potatoes, diced in 1/2-inch pieces\r\n2 C water\r\nSalt",
      "instructions": "Heat a medium saucepan to medium-high heat and melt butter.  Add onion, ginger and spices  Stir frequently 3-4 minutes, or until lightly browned and spices are fragrant.  Add remaining ingredients; season with salt.  Bring to a boil then reduce heat.  Simmer about 20 minutes, or until potatoes are almost tender.  Increase heat slightly until potatoes are tender and sauce has thickened, about 5-10 minutes longer.  Adjust seasoning to taste and serve hot over steamed basmati rice or with naan bread.",
