      "ingredients": "1 Tbs. olive oil\r\n2 leeks, white part only, sliced\r\n2 garlic cloves, minced\r\n1-1/2 C quartered crimini mushrooms\r\n1 C brown rice\r\n2 C chicken or vegetable stock\r\n1/2 tsp. salt\r\nBlack pepper to taste",
      "instructions": "Over medium heat, add olive oil to a medium saucepan.  Add leeks and garlic and cook 1-2 minutes.  Add crimini mushrooms; cook 3 minutes or until mushrooms soften slightly.  Stir in rice; cook until rice becomes slightly translucent, stirring occasionally, about 4 minutes.  Rice may brown slightly.\r\n     Stir in chicken stock and bring to a boil.  Add salt; reduce heat to medium-low.  Cover and cook 45-50 minutes or until rice is tender.  Stir in pepper and add more salt to taste.",
