      "id": 810,
      "name": "Almond Chicken Salad",
      "ingredients": "4 C cooked chicken\r\n1-1/2 C seedless green grapes, halved\r\n1 C chopped celery\r\n3/4 C sliced green onions\r\n1/2 C light Miracle Whip\r\n1/4 C fat-free sour cream\r\n1 Tbs. prepared mustard\r\n1 tsp. salt\r\n1/2 tsp. pepper\r\n1/4 tsp. onion powder\r\n1/4 tsp. celery salt\r\n1/8 tsp. ground mustard\r\n1/8 tsp. paprika\r\n1/2 C slivered almonds, toasted",
      "instructions": "In a large bowl, combine chicken, grapes, celery and onions. In another bowl, combine the next nine ingredients; stir until smooth.\r\n    Pour over the chicken mixture and toss gently. Stir in almonds and serve immediately, or refrigerate and add the almonds just before serving. Garnish with kiwi if desired.\r\n     Serving size is about 1/2 cup.",
