      "ingredients": "3 ripe avocados, halved and pitted\r\n1/2 C finely chopped Vidalia onion\r\n1/2 C snipped fresh cilantro\r\nJuice of 1 lime\r\nBottled hot pepper sauce, to taste\r\n1 Granny Smith apple, peeled, cored and finely chopped\r\nKosher salt or table salt, to taste",
      "instructions": "Scoop avocado flesh into a bowl; add the onion, cilantro, lime juice, and hot pepper sauce.  Mash with a fork until it reaches the desired consistency.  Stir in apple and season with salt to taste.",
