      "ingredients": "6 C frozen mixed berries\r\n1/2 C white sugar\r\n1-1/2 tsp. finely grated orange zest\r\n1/4 C orange juice\r\n2 Tbs. cornstarch\r\n2 Tbs. water",
      "instructions": "Stir together berries, sugar, zest, and juice in a slow cooker. Cook on High until bubbling, about 1-1/2 hours.\r\n     Stir together cornstarch and water in a cup until fully dissolved. Stir into berry mixture. Cook, covered, until thickened, 5 to 10 minutes more. Serve warm or room temperature.",
