      "name": "Korean Beef and Rice",
      "ingredients": "1 lb. lean ground beef\r\n3 garlic cloves, minced\r\n1/4 C packed brown sugar\r\n1/4 C reduced-sodium soy sauce\r\n2 tsp. sesame oil\r\n1/4 tsp. ground ginger\r\n1/4 tsp. crushed red pepper flakes\r\n1/4 tsp. pepper\r\n2-2/3 C hot cooked brown rice\r\n3 green onions, thinly sliced",
      "instructions": "In a large skillet, cook beef and garlic over medium heat 6-8 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, breaking up beef into crumbles. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix brown sugar, soy sauce, oil and seasonings.\r\n     Stir sauce into beef; heat through. Serve with rice. Sprinkle with green onions.",
